This guide describes how to install and use PCF Dev, a lightweight Pivotal Cloud Foundry&reg; (PCF) installation that runs on a single virtual machine (VM) on your workstation. PCF Dev is intended for application developers who want to develop and debug their applications locally on a PCF deployment. 

PCF Dev includes Pivotal Elastic Runtime, Redis, RabbitMQ, and MySQL. It also supports all CF CLI commands. See the [Comparing PCF Dev to Pivotal CF](#comparison-to-pcf) table below for more product details.

## <a id="prerequisites"></a>Prerequisites ##

* [Vagrant 1.8+](https://www.vagrantup.com/): Use Vagrant to run the development environment.
* [VirtualBox: 5.0+](https://www.virtualbox.org/): PCF Dev uses VirtualBox as its virtualizer.
* Latest version of [CF CLI](../pivotalcf/cf-cli/install-go-cli.html): Use CF CLI to push and scale apps.
* Internet connection required (for DNS)

